The values of the variables a, b, c are given. Calculate the value of the expression:

sqrt(a) + sqrt(|b-c|) / a**3 + b**2 + c**4

Write a function named expression that takes the values of the variables a, b, c as arguments and returns the value of the expression rounded to two decimal places.

Examples:

expression (1, 1, 1) should return 1;
expression (6, 1, 7) should return 2.45.

Solution:

function expression(a, b, c){
  return +(Math.sqrt(a) + Math.sqrt(Math.abs(b - c)) / (a ** 3 + b ** 2 + c ** 4)).toFixed(2);
}
